# Safe UI Implementation Process

This process exists because previous sessions caused multi-hour regressions from skipping steps. Follow every step in order.

## Golden Rule: Mockup first. Code last. Always.

## Process

### Step 1 — Screenshot current state
Before designing anything, look at the current state of the section being changed. Never assume what the UI looks like.

### Step 2 — Study carefully
Extract: exact column count, card dimensions, font sizes, colors, icon placement, class names, adjacent elements that must NOT be touched.

Common mistakes to avoid:
- Assuming 4-column grid when it is 2-column
- Making new cards different height than existing
- Adding scrollbars
- Letting content wrap to a second line

### Step 3 ep the exact code before designing
Run grep to find the real class names, IDs, and structure. Never guess.

### Step 4 — Build a mockup
Match exact grid, heights, padding, colors from existing UI. Show reference cards AND new cards together.

### Step 5 — Get explicit approval
Do NOT write any code until approval. If told "the size is off" — rebuild the mockup.

### Step 6 — Write surgical changes
Target only the exact HTML block. Never touch adjacent elements. Remove orphaned CSS.

### Step 7 — Verify with screenshot after
Check: new elements match mockup, no existing cards shifted/resized/broken, no scrollbars, nothing wraps, adjacent sections untouched.

Only declare complete after verification.

## PC Dashboard Card Style Reference
- Background: #1a1f2e
- Border radius: 10px
- Border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06)
- Icon: 16px, top left
- Number: 26-28px, bold, colored
- Label: 12px, #e2e8f0
- Sub: 10px, #64748b
- Ash accent border: 1px solid rgba(99,179,237,0.25)
- Ash badge: font-size:9px0a5fa; background:rgba(99,179,237,0.12); padding:1px 6px; border-radius:4px

## UI Standards
- overlay: rgba(0,0,0,0.75)
- modal-bg: #1e2530
- border-radius: 16px modals, 10px cards
- close button: plain X 20px #94a3b8
- primary button: var(--orange)
- input-bg: var(--surface2)
- slide panels: 440px wide
- modals: 420px (small) / 620px (large)
- z-index: panels=100, modals=1000, doc-viewer=2000, auth=9000+
- Never add scrollbars unless absolutely necessary
- Never let tab bars or meta rows wrap to two lines
